description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Dietitian with experience of Paediatric dietetics to join our friendly dietetic team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be based in the Ipswich Hospital (part of the ESNEFT) and form part of a team delivering paediatric dietetic care in both acute and community settings.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a valued member of the paediatric MDT you will have the opportunity to develop your skills covering the paediatric ward and outpatient clinics.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are a supportive team who have regular team meetings and have good links with surrounding trusts and paediatric teams.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be part of a team consisting of 26 Dietitians and 4 Dietetic Technicians/Assistants as well as Administrative and Secretarial staff working across both the acute and community sectors. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are a recognised department for student training in partnership with the University of Hertfordshire and high priority is given to the continuing professional development of our staff.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Catherine Dyson/Helen Gould, Professional Lead for Dietetics on 01473 704000 or Lindsey Mowles– Paediatric Dietitian on 01473 704002&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
